<p><b>Acceptable Use Policy</b></p>
<p>By using the website and/or other ("Services") provided by the non-profit organization Servants Code ("we," "us," "our," or "Servant's Code"), you ("you," "your," or "yours") agree to abide by the terms and restrictions of this Acceptable Use Policy (the "AUP"). The AUP is incorporated into any agreement (the "Agreement) between you and Servant's Code that references this AUP. We may modify or change this AUP at any time and provide you notice of such changes by posting the modified AUP to this site. Such modified AUP will become effective as to your use of the Services on the latter of (i) its posting to the site or (ii) as otherwise set forth in your Agreement. We reserves the right, but does not undertake the obligation, to investigate any violation of this AUP and to report any activity that we reasonably believes violates applicable law.</p>
<p>Violation of this AUP may lead to suspension or termination of your account and other actions, up to and including legal action. In addition, you may be required to pay for the costs of investigation and remedial action related to AUP violations. We reserve the right to take any other remedial action it sees fit.</p>
<p>We request that anyone with information about a violation of this AUP file a report via e-mail to the following address: enforcement@servantscode.org. Please provide the date and time (with time zone) of the violation and any identifying information regarding the violator, including e-mail or IP (Internet Protocol) address if available, as well as details of the violation.</p>
<p>You are independently responsible for your own compliance with all laws applicable to your conduct and your use of the Services. In addition, you agree not to engage in any of the following prohibited activities:</p>
<p><b>No Violation of the Security or Integrity of the Services or System; No Unauthorized Access.</b></p>
<p>You will not use the Services to violate the security or integrity of those Services or of any system used to provide the Services ("System"). You will not forge any packet header, email header, or any other portion of a message describing its origin or route. You will not use the Services, nor access the System used to provide the Services, without our authorization. You will not access any Service or restricted area within a Service or System to which you are not permitted access under your Agreement. You will not attempt to probe, scan, or test the security measures of the System used to provide the Services. You will not access or use the Services in a manner designed or intended to exceed usage quotas or limits placed upon your account, nor in any manner designed to avoid the incurrence of additional fees based on such use. You will not attempt to modify, alter, or otherwise create derivative works from any software to which you are provided access as part of your receipt of the Services, nor will you attempt to reverse engineer, reverse compile, decompile, disassemble, or deobfuscate such software, except where expressly permitted to do so by applicable law or the license agreement for any open source software used (if applicable).</p>
<p><b>No Interference with the Normal Function of the Services.</b></p>
<p>You will not use the Services or any System used to deliver the Services in any manner that interferes with or disrupts the Services or the System, including initiation of a Denial of Service attack or other high volume, automated attempt to access or deny access to the System or Services. You will neither insert nor permit the insertion of any Malicious Code and you will take all commercially reasonable actions and precautions to prevent the introduction or proliferation of any Malicious Code into the System used to provide the Services. "Malicious Code" will mean (i) any code, program, or sub‚Äêprogram, including any "virus", "Trojan horse", "worm", "trap door", "black box", or "malware" (as such terms are commonly understood in the computer software industry), or any other device or code designed to damage or maliciously interfere with the operation of the Services or System, or (ii) any device, method, or token that permits any person to circumvent without authorization the normal security of any software or system containing the code.</p>
<p><b>No Illegal, Harmful or Offensive Conduct.</b></p>
<p>You will not use the Services in any manner that violates any applicable law, including, without limitation, the uploading of content that violates the intellectual property or other proprietary rights of third parties. You will not use the Services, including by uploading any content, in a manner that is illegal, harmful, obscene, abusive, deceptive, harassing, defamatory, or offensive. You will not use the Services to violate the privacy rights of any person or to facilitate or cooperate in the dissemination of unsolicited bulk messages ("spam") in any way.</p>

